<subSubSection pageId="98" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="98.[729,1258,1117,1768]" pageId="98">
ETYMOLOGY: Because the species closely resembles 
<taxonomicName authorityName="BOSSELAERS &amp; JOCQUÉ" authorityYear="2000" box="[859,1054,1296,1319]" class="Arachnida" family="Corinnidae" genus="Hortipes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="98" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hormigricola">
<emphasis box="[859,1054,1296,1319]" italics="true" pageId="98">H. hormigricola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, it is called 
<taxonomicName authorityName="BOSSELAERS &amp; JOCQUÉ" authorityYear="2000" class="Arachnida" family="Corinnidae" genus="Hortipes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="98" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="depravator">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="98">depravator</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the counterfeiter.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="98" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="98.[729,1258,1117,1768]" pageId="98">
DIAGNOSIS: Males of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="BOSSELAERS &amp; JOCQUÉ" authorityYear="2000" box="[1031,1205,1356,1379]" class="Arachnida" family="Corinnidae" genus="Hortipes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="98" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="depravator">
<emphasis box="[1031,1205,1356,1379]" italics="true" pageId="98">H. depravator</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are easily recognized by the male palp with sharp­tipped femoral apophysis in combination with the gutter­shaped RTA and the long MA. Males differ from those of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="BOSSELAERS &amp; JOCQUÉ" authorityYear="2000" class="Arachnida" family="Corinnidae" genus="Hortipes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="98" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hormigricola">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="98">H. hormigricola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by shorter RTA, which is less strongly curved, and the distal end of the MA, which is not twisted.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
